The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Chateau Indage plans to open more than 1,000 outlets and sell more than 45 lakh litres of wine in the current fiscal. The company expects a turnover of over Rs 100 crore this fiscal, an official said. The outlets will specialise in selling and educating consumers about wines, he said. He, however, declined to comment on the investment planned for the expansion, which would be a mix of franchise and company-owned outlets and would be branded as Ivy wine bars.

 Kalpataru Power Transmission Ltd has recorded a 23 per cent increase in total revenue for the first quarter ended June 30 at Rs 373 crore compared with Rs 303 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. 

 Simplex Infrastructure has reported an 89 per cent jump in net profit for the first quarter ended June 30 at Rs 19.7 crore against Rs 10.4 crore in the year-ago period. The turnover jumped 69 per cent to Rs 594 crore.

 Tube Investments Ltd has reported sales of Rs 472.79 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 against Rs 413.55 crore in the year-ago period. The net profit for the quarter was Rs 14.09 crore.

 Monnet Ispat and Energy Ltd has recorded a net profit of Rs 48.55 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 26.64 crore in the year-ago period.

